 {"id":"bd-nn60","title":"Implement checkpoint API for progress reporting","description":"## Overview

Add checkpoint() and checkpoint_with() methods to Cx for tasks to report progress.

## API Design

```rust
impl Cx {
    /// Report progress toward completion.
    /// 
    /// This is used by the deadline monitoring system to detect
    /// stuck tasks. Call this periodically in long-running operations.
    /// 
    /// # Performance
    /// 
    /// This is a lightweight operation (updates a timestamp).
    /// Calling it frequently is fine.
    /// 
    /// # Example
    /// ```
    /// for item in items {
    ///     process(item).await;
    ///     cx.checkpoint();
    /// }
    /// ```
    pub fn checkpoint(&self) {
        self.checkpoint_with_impl(None);
    }

    /// Report progress with a descriptive message.
    /// 
    /// The message is included in warning logs if the task
    /// appears stuck, helping diagnose where it got stuck.
    /// 
    /// # Example
    /// ```
    /// for (i, batch) in batches.iter().enumerate() {
    ///     process_batch(batch).await;
    ///     cx.checkpoint_with(format!("batch {}/{}", i + 1, batches.len()));
    /// }
    /// ```
    pub fn checkpoint_with(&self, msg: impl Into<String>) {
        self.checkpoint_with_impl(Some(msg.into()));
    }

    fn checkpoint_with_impl(&self, msg: Option<String>) {
        let now = Instant::now();
        let mut state = self.inner.checkpoint_state.lock();
        state.last_checkpoint = now;
        state.last_message = msg;
        state.checkpoint_count += 1;
    }
}
```

## Checkpoint State

```rust
#[derive(Default)]
pub(crate) struct CheckpointState {
    /// When the last checkpoint was recorded.
    pub last_checkpoint: Option<Instant>,

    /// Message from the last checkpoint.
    pub last_message: Option<String>,

    /// Total checkpoints recorded.
    pub checkpoint_count: u64,
}
```

